question: What about them fighting 'cause Harry thinks her outfit isn't appropriate and doesn't want to let her leave the house like that
answer:
“What the fuck you think you’re wearing?” Harry yelled at his wife who was dressed nicely in a red dress hugging her curves, her thickness made him feel the prominent tightness in his pants but he was too busy on her clothing. He was turned out but furious too as what she was wearing for a dinner party that wasn’t too fancy.

“A dress actually.” She said rolling her eyes walking past him to grab a bottle of water from it and chunking it down. She knew how possessive harry was, he never approved her of low cuts or too short skirts. Always said how those were the things only supposed to be seen by harry.

“Change it.” He said sternly.

“No.”

“I said change it.”

“I’m going like this. You like it or not. And if you have that much problem with my dressing, I might just stay home.” She said rather loudly turning back on her heels making way to their bedroom, her hands coming in contact with the chain of her dress unzipping it already but harry was quick to spin her around pulling to his chest. His slender fingers caressing her naked back ever so softly before zipping her back up again.

He leaned on brushing his lips on his ear so tenderly that it made her practically shiver, goosebumps prominent on her skin.

“I don’t have a problem with it, just scared that you wont be able to walk properly tomorrow. Gonna fuck you so hard”

summary:
Behind everything.
In which Harry reminds you that you’re his home.
***
“M’ going to work, stop tha’”
Harry tried to wiggle out...
body:
Behind everything.

In which Harry reminds you that you’re his home.

***

“M’ going to work, stop tha’”

Harry tried to wiggle out from your grasp, as you let out a high pitched giggle. It was another day in the studio for Harry, and you guys didn’t have the chance spend time for each other.

“But, you kept on going to the studio for two weeks now! I need cuddles.” You whined, pressing your cheeks on his back; not letting him go.

A smile went up to Harry’s lips as he saw your reflection in the mirror, your hair was a mess, your mood was becoming gloomy, and your arms were tightly around his waist, probably leaving a wrinkled spot around it.

He can’t help but turn her around, cupping her face on his both hands, and gave her forehead a long loving kiss and he hugged her tightly, making sure there were no space left between them.

“M’ just gonna continue some of my few songs, poppet.” He whispered trying to calm her down.

“When I’m finished, I swear to God, I’m all yours.” She closed her eyes for a moment, savoring all of his touches, because after 30 minutes, she won’t feel it anymore.

Missing him was normal, especially when he goes on tour, but you’re not used to when you’re not feeling his touch, not being to hear his voice while you fell asleep. It hurt you the most when you can’t even his presence.

“Help me choose an outfit to wear, yeah?” He politely asked and started to get up the bed as he went to his closet.

“Just a t-shirt and your trousers will be fiiine.” You said and started to lay again on the bed, hugging his pillow. You hummed in satisfaction when you inhaled all of his scent. It was so arousing.

He started fixing his hair and started to get his shoes, you bit your lip as you saw his back muscles reflexing every movements he make, it was hot and a turn on for you.

You were busy checking him out until you realized he was prepared and ready to go, you sat up from the bed as you watched him go to the bathroom getting his perfume.

“I’ll be home as soon as I can, okay?” He ressured you, You let out a sigh and walked up to him, fixing his necklace and wrapping your arms around his neck.

“It’s okay, that studio is your happiness. go there and do what you want to do. I want your album to be successful.” You murmured, giving him a smile.

Harry leaned in and gave your lips a sweet kiss, holding your cheeks as he pulled you closer. He loves your lips connecting to his own, loving how it moves together in sync.

“The studio is not my happiness, sweetheart.”

he paused.

“You. You are my happiness, and home. So whatever happens, always expect me running back to you.”
